george pesut. In the 1980-81 season, he resurfaced back in North America on the comeback trail, trying out with the NHL's Edmonton Oilers and eventually signing a one year contract with their farm team, the Wichita Wind, in the Central Hockey League where back in old form, he put up 3 goals and 21 assists with the Wind, for a total of 27 points. Awards, honors and accomplishments.- Best Defenceman Award Western Canada Hockey League (WCHL Major Junior) 1972-73 season;
- First Team All-Star WCHL, 1972-73;
- High Selection Draft Pick- 24th overall in both the NHL Draft and WHA Draft to the St. Louis Blues and Cleveland Crusaders respectively;
- Only rookie selected for Stanley Cup Champion Philadelphia Flyers (Broad Street Bullies) opening night roster, 1974-75;
- Voted the Best Defenceman in Swiss hockey three consecutive seasons;
- Played two full 60 minute games, end to end, an accomplishment never before accomplished in Swiss hockey;
- German Championship winner with Berlin, first team All-star for consecutive seasons in Germany. Life in the Bay Area.

